Dataset Description
The Triagegeist dataset is a synthetic emergency department triage dataset generated by the Laitinen-Fredriksson Foundation for research and educational purposes. All records are fully simulated. No real patient data is included. The dataset is designed to reflect the statistical distributions and clinical relationships observed in published emergency medicine literature.

The dataset covers a simulated 24-month period across a fictional multi-site hospital network and contains structured intake data, free-text chief complaint narratives, and disposition outcomes.

Files
File	Format	Description
train.csv	CSV	Training set. Contains patient intake features and triage acuity label.
test.csv	CSV	Test set. Contains patient intake features without acuity label.
chief_complaints.csv	CSV	Free-text chief complaint narratives linked to records via patient_id.
sample_submission.csv	CSV	A valid submission file in the required format.
Columns: train.csv and test.csv
Column	Type	Description
patient_id	string	Unique patient identifier. Links to chief_complaints.csv.
arrival_mode	categorical	Mode of arrival: ambulance, walk-in, transfer, police.
arrival_hour	integer	Hour of arrival (0-23).
arrival_day	categorical	Day of week: Monday through Sunday.
age	integer	Patient age in years.
sex	categorical	M, F, Other.
systolic_bp	float	Systolic blood pressure (mmHg) at triage.
diastolic_bp	float	Diastolic blood pressure (mmHg) at triage.
heart_rate	float	Heart rate (bpm) at triage.
respiratory_rate	float	Respiratory rate (breaths/min) at triage.
temperature_c	float	Body temperature in Celsius at triage.
spo2	float	Peripheral oxygen saturation (%) at triage.
gcs_total	integer	Glasgow Coma Scale total score (3-15).
pain_score	integer	Self-reported pain score (0-10). Missing values encoded as -1.
num_prior_visits	integer	Number of prior ED visits in the past 12 months.
triage_acuity	integer	Target variable (train only). ESI level 1-5. 1 = most urgent, 5 = least urgent.
Columns: chief_complaints.csv
Column	Type	Description
patient_id	string	Links to train.csv and test.csv.
chief_complaint_raw	string	Raw free-text chief complaint as entered by triage nurse.
Missing Values
Missing values are present in systolic_bp, diastolic_bp, heart_rate, respiratory_rate, temperature_c, spo2, and pain_score. Missingness is not random and reflects realistic triage conditions in which certain vitals are not obtained for lower-acuity patients. Participants should document their imputation strategy.

