Synthetic Data Notice
All records are entirely synthetic. No real patient data is included. Distributions were calibrated to reflect patterns reported in published emergency medicine literature (MIMIC-IV-ED, NHAMCS, ESI validation studies).

Files
File	Rows	Cols	Description
train.csv	80,000	40	Features + target (triage_acuity)
test.csv	20,000	37	Features, no target
chief_complaints.csv	100,000	3	Free-text triage complaints
patient_history.csv	100,000	26	Binary comorbidity flags
sample_submission.csv	20,000	2	Submission format example
All files join on patient_id.

Target Variable
triage_acuity — ESI level 1–5. 1 = most urgent, 5 = least urgent.

Key Columns
Vitals: systolic_bp, diastolic_bp, mean_arterial_pressure, pulse_pressure, heart_rate, respiratory_rate, temperature_c, spo2, gcs_total, pain_score, shock_index, news2_score, bmi

Demographics: age, age_group, sex, language, insurance_type

Triage context: arrival_mode, arrival_hour, shift, arrival_season, transport_origin, mental_status_triage, chief_complaint_system, pain_location

History: num_prior_ed_visits_12m, num_prior_admissions_12m, num_active_medications, num_comorbidities

Outcomes (train only): disposition, ed_los_hours

Comorbidities (patient_history.csv): 25 binary hx_ flags including hypertension, diabetes, copd, heart_failure, dementia, malignancy, and others.

Missing Values
Missingness is clinically realistic, not random. systolic_bp, diastolic_bp, and respiratory_rate are more frequently missing in lower-acuity patients. pain_score uses -1 (not NaN) when not recorded.

